  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COFFEE REVIVAL PROJECT- Quality Coffee, Better Livelihoods</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Form new Village Savings and Loan Associations (VSLAs) and strengthen existing ones
- Provide mobile banking services to coffee farmers
- Mobilize farmers to subscribe to crop insurance
- Train farmers in safe use of agro inputs in partnership with input suppliers
- Support six certified coffee nurseries and agroforestry tree nurseries
- Train farmers in quality aspects</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farming communities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of the project is to improve the livelihoods of men and women smallholder farmers and their families in Greater Mpigi area through sustainable Robusta coffee production. To contribute to this goal, the project strategic objective is that targeted Robusta coffee farmers increase their income from coffee sales. The outcomes are:
- Targeted farmers have increased Robusta coffee productivity and quality.
- MBUGO ACE (the local cooperative) provides sustainable and fair/equitable service to farmers alongthe Robusta coffee value chain
- Targeted farmers access sustainable Robusta coffee markets</narrative>
  </description>
